if state of css

    // Javascript
    if (condition) {
    // Some JS that will run if the condition is met.
    }

    /* CSS */
    @media (condition) {
    /* Some CSS that'll run if the condition is met. */
    }

    examples - 


        @media (max-width: 300px) {
            .small-only {
                color: red;
            }
        }


        @media (min-width: 300px) {
            .large-screens {
            display: block;
            }
            .small-screens {
            display: none;
            }
        }


    Valid conditions - 

        max-width and min-width are media feature. In the context of a media query, max-width is a ‚Äúmedia feature‚Äù, not a CSS property. They
        just happen to share the same name.Not all CSS properties have corresponding media features. For example, this snippet 
        is not valid:



            /* üö´ Not valid, since `font-size` can't be queried */
                @media (font-size: 32px) {
            }